To control your voice-controlled robot, follow these steps to connect your smartphone via Bluetooth using the ARM_Voice app:

Instructions
Download the App
Go to Google play store and search for the app called ARM_Voice.
Download and install the app on your smartphone.
Power On Your Robot
Turn on your robot using an external power supply.
Enable Bluetooth on Your Phone
Ensure Bluetooth is turned on in your smartphone's settings.
Connect to the Bluetooth Module
Open the ARM_Voice app on your smartphone.
Select the 'HC-05 Bluetooth Module' option from the app.


Observe the red light on the Bluetooth module. It will change from fast blinking to a slow blinking gesture, indicating a successful connection between your smartphone and the robot.
